      "identifier": "startram_boundary_collapse",
      "summary": "Startram module collapses domain, infrastructure, and persistence boundaries into one hub.",
      "related_files": [
        "goseg/startram/startram.go",
        "goseg/config/version.go"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "`startram/startram.go` handles API orchestration (`Register`, `SvcCreate`, `Alias*`, `Retrieve`), config mutation (`config.UpdateConfTyped`), restore persistence (`os.WriteFile`, `os.MkdirAll`), and runtime infrastructure (`exec.Command(\"docker\", ...)`) in one module.",
        "The same broad side-effect pattern exists in `config/version.go`, where remote fetch and local persistence/global-state mutation are tightly coupled inside one package API (`SyncVersionInfo`).",
        "This shared pattern indicates architectural drift toward side-effect-heavy hub modules instead of separated adapters and application services."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Split startram into explicit layers: API client adapter, registration application service, and backup/restore infrastructure service; similarly keep version fetching separate from persistence/state publication to restore one-way dependency flow.",
