      "identifier": "transport_schema_leaks_across_boundary",
      "summary": "WebSocket transport payload types leak from handler layer into importer workflow boundary.",
      "related_files": [
        "goseg/handler/upload.go",
        "goseg/startram/startram.go"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "`UploadHandler` unmarshals websocket message into `structs.WsUploadPayload` and passes that full payload directly to `importer.SetUploadSession`, tying importer behavior to handler transport schema.",
        "In `startram/startram.go`, public workflow functions similarly operate directly on config/network DTO concerns (`config.Conf()` and API request structs inside service-level functions) instead of receiving boundary-neutral commands.",
        "Both patterns indicate missing translation layer between transport/config representations and core use-case inputs."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Introduce use-case command structs decoupled from websocket/API DTOs (e.g., `OpenUploadEndpointCmd`, `RegisterServiceCmd`), and perform all message/config translation only at boundary adapters (handler/client packages).",
